The paper deals with computational complexity of inferences in statistical models, specifically credal networks. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as these fields heavily rely on statistical models for decision-making and prediction. The paper also discusses the concept of independence, which is a fundamental concept in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes new results and settles open questions, which is a common theme in systems and control (cs.SI).
